<h3>Aeotec NanoMote Quad</h3>
<!-- from https://products.z-wavealliance.org/products/2817 -->
<p>Once you‚Äôve added the NanoMote to your z-wave network, you‚Äôll need to update your zwcfg_*.xml file with the below xml data. Stop Home Assistant and open your zwcfg_*.xml file (located in your config folder). Find the NanoMote device section and then its corresponding <code>CommandClass</code> section with id=‚Äú91‚Äù. Replace the entire CommandClass section with the below xml data. Save the file and restart Home Assistant.</p>
<pre><code class="language-xml">    &lt;CommandClass id=&quot;91&quot; name=&quot;COMMAND_CLASS_CENTRAL_SCENE&quot; version=&quot;1&quot; request_flags=&quot;4&quot; innif=&quot;true&quot; scenecount=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
